# AUTH command tests - Authenticate with password
@name AUTH
@group connection
@since 1.0.0

=== TEST: AUTH without password configured
RUN:
AUTH mypassword
EXPECT:
(error) ERR invalid password

=== TEST: AUTH wrong number of arguments
RUN:
AUTH
EXPECT:
(error) ERR wrong number of arguments for 'auth' command

=== TEST: AUTH multiple arguments
RUN:
AUTH password extra
EXPECT:
(error) ERR syntax error

=== TEST: AUTH empty password
RUN:
AUTH ""
EXPECT:
(error) ERR invalid password

=== TEST: AUTH returns error when no auth configured
RUN:
AUTH wrongpassword
EXPECT:
(error) ERR invalid password
